<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="950" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d950">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.00/8–246: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-02">August 2, 1946</date>.<lb/>[Received August
                                2—1:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>357. Council of Ministers yesterday approved (1) broad political amnesty
                            (2) right of workers to organize in principle (3) participation of
                            Communist Party in politics.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Beaulac</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>